RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANNA'S IMAGE tracked the leader between horses up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and drew off in the lane. UNCAPTURED DREAMS led the field on the inside up the backstretch, continued to show the way while racing in the two path around the bend, was caught in upper stretch and kept on to the wire. SORTARIA raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn and gained ground late, no threat to the winner. SUNSHINE GIRL raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path and finished evenly. THE MONEY MACHINE raced off the pace on the inside early, saved ground around the bend and made no bid. BANK BUSTER pressed the pace on the outside through the opening stages, raced in the two path around the turn and faded in the lane. MOVE TO ORDER raced in the middle of the pack between horses early, dropped back while racing in the two path around the turn and continued to tire in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 18600. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 29 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since November 29 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHARGING AERO veered out leaving the gate, recovered to chase the leader on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, began a bid passing the quarter pole and edged clear late. DRAMA'S PRAYER led the field on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to show the way from the two path coming around the bend, dueled in the stretch and was caught near the wire. CARRONADE raced off the pace between horses up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and finished evenly. AWESOME ENOUGH hit the gate leaving it, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, improved position in upper stretch and flattened out in the final furlong. TAP FIRST tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and faded in the lane. BLANK'S HAT TRICK raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, made no bid and was vanned off post race after pulling up in distress.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 73. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $20,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horse s Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SINGALONG KAYLA saved ground around the first turn, led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way racing around the far turn in the two path and held off a closer in late stretch. GALLEY HEAD saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the second turn from the two path, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground steadily to the wire. ACE UP HER SLEEVE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from the three path coming around the far bend, and flattened out in the lane. SILVER SPRINTER saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and never threatened. LIVELY REMARK raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, came around the second bend still in the two path and faded in the stretch. I'LL GO ALL IN raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path and made no bid. GET IT trailed the field from the two path through the opening half mile, dropped back further while saving ground around the far turn and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 29 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since November 29 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPEED WAY trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, began a bid passing the eighth pole and quickly went from last to first to pull clear at the finish. SHANGHAI WARRIOR chased the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, challenged from the two path around the turn, kicked clear in upper stretch and was caught late. JAMA DILLON raced off the pace early, navigated the turn from the two path, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and improved position in the lane. I'LL FINISH led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the bend and tired in the final furlong. AIDINGANDABETTING tracked the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn and weakened in the lane. COMPASS CAY raced in the middle of the pack on the outside in the early going, navigated the bend from the four path and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 68. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $32,000 OR LESS OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $32,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since November 29 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Fort y Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOVE FOREVERAFTER raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace, navigated the far turn from the four path, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground steadily to get up for the win late. SAWEETIE GIRL saved ground around the first turn, led the field up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far turn and in upper stretch and was caught in the final strides. SUPER CARO raced in the middle of the pack in the two path through the opening half mile, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn and gained ground late, just missing second. X Y LADY raced in the three path around the first bend, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, angled in to save ground around the far turn and finished evenly. MEDIATION raced in the two path early, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the far bend and tired in the stretch. ELSA'S ROCKET reared up leaving the gate, trailed the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the second turn and made no bid.

ENTRY.NAME: Love Foreverafter
ENTRY.OWNER: Seltzer, Edward A. and Anderson, Beverly S.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 19500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: R TOOTSIE GLITTER led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and dug in gamely in the stretch to hold the win. STORMIN' AMANDA broke through the gate prior to the race, was away quickly, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the two and three path coming around the bend and dueled to the wire but could not get by the winner. CLASSIC DREAMER raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, came around the turn in the five path and improved position late. LANCE'S SMILE raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and was outkicked in the lane. PARTY DREAM raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the opening stages, continued around the turn in the two path and offered no kick. WISHIN N KISSIN raced off the pace up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and never threatened. JUST MERCY raced in the middle of the pack between horses early, navigated the bend from the four path and tired in the stretch. TRAIN WRECK trailed the field between horses up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and made no bid. ARAUCARIA veered out leaving the gate, settled at the back of the pack through the opening quarter, raced in the three path around the turn and was empty from there. PER RULING #2023-009295 FROM THE FLORIDA RACING COMMISSION, R TOOTSIE GLITTER WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM 1st TO UNPLACED DUE TO A POSITIVE TEST.

Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Sin ce Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HEREBY saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path, launched a bid approaching the quarter pole and got up for the win late. GET EVEN saved ground around the first turn, led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way racing in the two path around the far bend and dueled in the stretch, getting caught in the final strides. STREET GLIDE raced in the three path early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the inside, saved ground around the far turn and improved position in late stretch. DIAL HIM UP raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn and improved position in the lane. URBAN BEACH raced off the pace on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far bend still in the two path and made a mild improvement of position in the stretch. TIMMINS raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and finished evenly while never threatening. LORD OF THE NILE raced in the four path through the opening quarter of a mile, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, came around the second bend in the three path and was outkicked in the stretch. WICKED MOMENT raced in the two path around the first bend, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and tired in the lane. LANCELOT LYNK trailed the field from the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far bend and was never a factor. SING ME AN ALIBI raced at the back of the pack in the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dropped back to trail well behind the field while saving ground around the second turn and was eased to the wire.

ENTRY.OWNER: Meier IV Robert A and Taylor Mark F

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 97. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 27000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $16,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 29 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since November 29 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MORGAN POINT dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn and drew off in the lane. HAPPY CAJUN chased the leaders on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, raced into mild traffic while saving ground around the turn, could not go with the winner in the stretch and kept on to the wire while drifting mildly. SAN COSTANTINO stalked the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the bend and chased the winner home in the stretch. CONFESSOR tracked the leaders between horses early, navigated the turn from the two path and faded in the lane. BLAKENSTEIN dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the bend and tired in the stretch. GOT EM THINKING trailed the field the entire way around the oval, raced in the two and three path around the turn and was never a factor. THE RIDER OF HORSE TWO, HAPPY CAJUN, FILED AN OBJECTION AGAINST HORSE FIVE, MORGAN POINT, CLAIMING INTERFERENCE ON THE FAR TURN. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.NAME: Got Em Thinking
ENTRY.OWNER: Rodriguez Juan D and Rodriguez Jesus

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 9 1M Turf CR: 85. Claiming Purse 17100. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 29 Allowed 2 lbs. ; Such A Race Since November 29 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12, 500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VETERANS BEACH raced in the two path around the first turn, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the far turn and kicked clear in the stretch. SIMMS was bumped and forced to steady leaving the gate, trailed the field while saving ground through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the two path, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. BIG RED ROCKS saved ground around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and improved position in the lane. EIGHT WEEKS LONG raced in the two path around the first turn, stalked the leader between horses up the backstretch, challenged from the two path around the second turn and weakened late. SKIPPERINI raced in the middle of the pack on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the three path and finished evenly. FREELANCE raced in the three path early, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, came around the far turn still in the three path and showed no kick. PUTMAN bumped with the horse to his inside at the start, raced in the two path around the first turn, led the way between horses up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far bend and faded in the lane. CLASSIC BET fought his rider while saving ground around the first turn, settled in to track the leader on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far turn and was empty from there. CROWLEY'S WAR chased the leader on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the two path around the second bend and tired further in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Crowley's War
ENTRY.OWNER: Breeze Easy LLC and Wismer Glenn S
